snippet.textDisplay:
Many of the top US heavyweight fighters in the few years before Wilder came along / reached his prime were fat bums, so I understand why some people in the US media have overhyped him. Any sport is better off when there a strong US contenders to keep the biggest market in the world interested.

However his record is laughably padded out, and he has basically fought a bunch of tomato cans for much of his career. Who is the second best opponent that he has beaten after a 38-40 year old Ortiz? Crickets. It’s a joke to compare him to Fury or Joshua, he’s not in their league.
